<header>
  <h1>Beach Wedding FAQ</h1>
  <p>Planning a Gulf Coast celebration? Here are answers to common questions about permits, timing, weather, and logistics.</p>
</header>

<main>
  <section class="faq" aria-label="Frequently Asked Questions">
    <h2>Your Questions, Answered</h2>

    <details>
      <summary>Do we need a beach permit for our ceremony?</summary>
      <div class="content">
        <p>Many Gulf Coast beaches require a special event permit for ceremonies, arches, or seating. Rules differ by city and park. We'll help identify whether a permit is needed and suggest the best access points for your group size.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>What's the best time of day for a beach wedding?</summary>
      <div class="content">
        <p><strong>Golden hour</strong> (about 1-2 hours before sunset) offers flattering light, cooler temps, and beautiful photos. Mornings are quieter with softer light; midday can be bright and warm.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>What if it rains or there's inclement weather?</summary>
      <div class="content">
        <p>We always recommend a backup like a covered pavilion or nearby indoor space. We monitor the forecast and can adjust timing when feasible. Your coordinator will walk you through options in advance.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>How many guests can we have?</summary>
      <div class="content">
        <p>Capacity depends on the specific beach access, parking, and local guidelines. Intimate elopements fit almost anywhere; for larger groups we'll recommend beaches with more space and amenities.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Can you help with photography, flowers, and decor?</summary>
      <div class="content">
        <p>Yes - our packages include essentials and optional upgrades like bouquets, arches, tiki torches, and extended photo coverage. We'll tailor everything to your style and location.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Is the beach accessible for guests with limited mobility?</summary>
      <div class="content">
        <p>Many locations feature ramps, boardwalks, or close parking. Tell us your needs and we'll guide you to the most accessible spots around Clearwater, St. Pete Beach, and Sarasota.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>How do Florida marriage licenses work?</summary>
      <div class="content">
        <p>Marriage licenses are issued by Florida county clerks. Requirements and timelines can vary slightly by county. We'll point you to the correct clerk's office for your chosen beach and help you understand the steps.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Can we customize a package?</summary>
      <div class="content">
        <p>Absolutely. You can add photo coverage, arches, seating, unity ceremonies, and more. Share your vision and we'll create a plan that fits your style and budget.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Which beaches do you serve?</summary>
      <div class="content">
        <p>We frequently serve Clearwater Beach, Sand Key Park, St. Pete Beach, Pass-A-Grille, Fort De Soto, Indian Rocks, Madeira Beach, Redington, Siesta Key, Lido Beach, Anna Maria Island, and more.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <p class="muted">Have a question that's not listed? <a href="index.html#contact">Contact us</a> - we're happy to help.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact Form (same as index) -->
  <section id="contact" aria-labelledby="contact-title">
